      • checkEligibility

        public abstract int checkEligibility​(String spId)
        Checks whether a device supports the pan-payment function. The multi-user status of the device and its prop configuration are read and checked.
        Parameters:
        spId - The id to differentiate the caller
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the device supports the pan-payment function; returns other values otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • syncSeInfo

        public abstract int syncSeInfo​(String spId,
                               String sign,
                               String timeStamp)
        Synchronizes the supplementary security domain information of a chip. This method is used to update the device security domain status on the server without uploading the security domain information.
        Parameters:
        spId - Indicates the caller ID.
        sign - Indicates the signature of the operation to be performed.
        timeStamp - Indicates the timestamp in yyyyMMddHHmmss format.
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the synchronization is successful; returns other values otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • createSSD

        public abstract int createSSD​(String spId,
                              String sign,
                              String timeStamp,
                              String ssdAid)
        Creates an supplementary security domain for storing information.
        Parameters:
        spId - Indicates the caller ID.
        sign - Indicates the signature of the operation to be performed.
        timeStamp - Indicates the timestamp in yyyyMMddHHmmss format.
        ssdAid - Indicates the ID of the supplementary security domain to be created, which is configured by Huawei.
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the supplementary security domain is created; returns other values otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • deleteSSD

        public abstract int deleteSSD​(String spId,
                              String sign,
                              String timeStamp,
                              String ssdAid)
        Deletes an supplementary security domain. Calling this method also deletes the information stored in the supplementary security domain.
        Parameters:
        spId - Indicates the caller ID.
        sign - Indicates the signature of the operation to be performed.
        timeStamp - Indicates the timestamp in yyyyMMddHHmmss format.
        ssdAid - Indicates the ID of the supplementary security domain to be deleted.
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the supplementary security domain is deleted; returns other values otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • commonExecute

        public abstract int commonExecute​(String spId,
                                  String serviceId,
                                  String funCallId)
        Performs a user-defined operation and issues different chip instructions according to funCallId. You can perform a user-defined operation based on the service ID and function ID on which you have reached an agreement with the trusted service manager (TSM).
        Parameters:
        spId - Indicates the caller ID.
        serviceId - Indicates the server session ID.
        funCallId - Indicates the ID of the operation to be performed.
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the operation is successful; returns other values otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • getCplc

        public abstract String getCplc​(String spId)
        Obtains the Card Production Life Cycle (CPLC) data of a chip. Call this interface to get cplc information
        Parameters:
        spId - Indicates the caller ID.
        Returns:
        Returns the CPLC data in character string format; returns null otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • isEnable

        public abstract boolean isEnable​(String spId,
                                 String info)
        Checks whether pan-payment is enabled. If pan-payment is disabled, many operations are unavailable. You need to ensure that the switch is in the open state before performing the operation.
        Parameters:
        spId - Indicates the caller ID.
        info - Indicates information related to HUAWEI Wallet. An empty string is input if HUAWEI Wallet is not used.
        Returns:
        Returns the pan-payment status matching the caller ID, true means switch on.
        Since:
        1

      • setEnable

        public abstract int setEnable​(String spId,
                              String info,
                              boolean isEnable)
        Sets the pan-payment switch status. If pan-payment switch is off, many operations are unavailable.
        Parameters:
        spId - Indicates the caller ID.
        info - Indicates information related to HUAWEI Wallet. An empty string is input if HUAWEI Wallet is not used.
        isEnable - Indicates the status to be set, true means switch on.
        Returns:
        Returns 0 if the pan-payment status is set; returns other values otherwise.
        Since:
        1

        Returns:

      • setConfig

        public abstract int setConfig​(String spId,

        Parameters:
